metadata.name: Oyoyiz #181
metadata.description:
Oyoyiz is an abstract composition generator. Available in 8 different color palettes and 2 styles (Organic and Brutalist), shapes made of a random number of segments are displayed on a grid. The name Oyoyiz was randomly generated.

Coded with Processing and P5js in October 2022 by @eltono and Michel - www.eltono.com

metadata.name: Clutch #51
metadata.description:
Halftones, dynamic composition and high color contrasts for a groovy composition inspired by action b-movies, their posters and music.

Semi-realtime javascript / webgl.
Desktop / Chrome recommended.

You can find more infos about the project in the fx(text) linked below.

Controls :
- Press [SPACE] to show/hide the user interface
- Mouse wheel/middle/ Pinch : Zoom
- After zooming, Mouse left / Drag : Pan

Keyboard shortcuts and additionnal instructions : 
- [R]eset the camera.
- Toggle the [F]rame.
- Unlock the [C]amera, with rotation on Mouse2.
- Export a PNG capture at various resolutions by pressing the number keys [1] to [9] (top row or numpad, and only in live mode, after pressing "open"). I recommend starting with [4] and going from there. What is captured is what's on screen, so you can get creative if you so desire.

NFT License

metadata.name: Hydro Gen #122
metadata.description:
Against the backdrop of texts about valuing water, Hydro Gen charts the ecological devastation and eventual revival of the Tisza river following what has been called one of the gravest environmental disasters in central Europe since Chernobyl.

Nature and humans here are bound within a single frame — havoc in the ecological system activates the breakdown of meaning in the human signifying system of language, but hidden in the wave of ecological disaster is a (re)generative love poem to water that bears witness to its multifaceted beauty and power. A second poem is generated as a soundtrack based on the displayed background text.

- - - - - CLICK TO START SOUND - - - - -

Hydro Gen is a collaborative work conceptualized and developed over the course of one week as part of NFT DEB Generative Dimensions 2022 Hackathon and Conference.

Kalen Iwamoto, lead artist, director

Vitalii Shumanskyi, lead programmer

Nayven Vignette, audio programmer

Tamás Béke, data analysis and visualization

metadata.name: EDDY #13
metadata.description:
An eddy is a circular movement of water counter to a main current. It reminds me of innovations in art, like a small countercurrent to the mainstream, surfacing new techniques and aesthetics. 

I hope that EDDY will brighten your days with its playful swirl of colors, inspired by the sea, the sky, the birds, and post-impressionist paintings.

Keyboard Controls:
[F] Fill the window.
[S] Save the current view in live mode as an image (default 1125x1500px).
[1] [2] [4] [6] Change resolution, 1.5K to 9K.
[R] Reverse course.

Made with p5js and shaders.

Created by elsif, 2022.12.

metadata.name: d/e/m/boss invaders #79
metadata.description:
Invaders is an algorithm that builds rows of rectangles and plays with repetition, colors and depth order.
Outputs reminds me space invaders, but some looks like motherboard circuits, temples, or just a overhead map from a hotel room emergency exit

Please be patient, it takes a while to render (25-45 secs) and draws around 6M circles during 4 steps.

Responsive, zoom out browser window and refresh to get a larger output.
's' save the current canvas

Invaders is part of a series playing with textures creating emboss/deboss effect.

de/
 /boss
em/

100% code, made with p5js
See License.md

metadata.name: F.T.B.A #58
metadata.description:
https://rhaegarart.com/f-t-b-a/

A generative art that tries to express the difference between reality and unreality.

This project is coded in an optimized way. The main code is written with just 36 lines of code. The total js code with fxFeatures is 61 lines.

Features:

- 2 Background styles: Dark & Bright
- 4 Texture intensities: Low-Medium-High-Very High
- 3 Noise complexities: Low-Medium-High
- 4 Noise amounts: Low-Medium-High-Very High
- 2 Noise positions: Over the cuts & Beyond the Cuts
- 4 Cut intensities: Low-Medium-High-Very High
- 13 Cut styles: Youth-Imagination-Tale-Onion-Family-Wood-Library-Chocolate-Gate-Tradition-Lake-Reflection-Paper
- 3 Cut width: Low-Medium-High
- 28 Different color palettes
- 2 Different color directions

Warning! Loading might take up to 40 seconds as your machine's power. Also, your browser might not respond during the loading stage. Please be patient till the end.

The project was tested on desktop Chrome 106.0.5249.119, Mozilla 105.0.3, and Edge 106.0.1370.42 versions.

Press 's' to export a high-res png file in live mode.

Made with p5js and WebGL shaders.

CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 LICENSE

November 2022 / Rhaegar

metadata.name: Artifice #294
metadata.description:
This series is is about playful obfuscation.

The fxtext article linked on the main profect goes more in-depth into what is meant by that, as well as the events that led to this collection.

5640 bytes of Vanilla JS with no libraries. Palettes make up a third of the code.

In live mode:
‘S’ : save as png (3000 × 3600)
’V’ : save as svg (without grain)

URL params in live mode:
‘g=n’ : no grain
‘g=p’ : paper grain
‘h=t’ : high resolution mode, 9000 ×10600 (Chrome only, and may take a moment)

For example, if you wanted paper grain in high resolution, append “&g=p&h=t” to the url in live mode.

After rendering with these params, tapping 'P' will then save a png with those settings applied.
